# Cursor AI Rules for Najm Rush Project

## Project Overview
This is a Next.js 16 project for Najm Rush Contracting company website, built with App Router, Tailwind CSS v4, and modern web technologies.

## Code Style
- Use Arabic comments for business logic
- Use English for technical comments
- Follow ESLint and Prettier configurations
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer TypeScript for new components (when possible)

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `ProjectCard`)
- Files: camelCase for utilities, PascalCase for components
- Functions: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

## Architecture
- Use App Router for all pages
- Keep components in `/components` folder
- Static data in `/data` folder
- Images in `/public/images` folder
- Use environment variables for configuration

## Component Patterns
- Use named exports for components
- Export components as default when they're the main export
- Use descriptive prop names
- Add JSDoc comments for complex components

## Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Prefer responsive design with mobile-first approach
- Use semantic color names from Tailwind
- Avoid inline styles, use className instead

## Performance Considerations
- Use Next.js Image component for images
- Implement proper loading states
- Use React.memo for expensive components when needed
- Optimize bundle size by lazy loading

## Error Handling
- Use Error Boundaries for graceful error handling
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Log errors appropriately in production

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Add proper ARIA labels when needed
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Test with screen readers

## Best Practices
- Implement proper error handling
- Add loading states for async operations
- Use semantic HTML
- Ensure responsive design
- Optimize images and performance
- Follow accessibility guidelines

## Security
- Never commit sensitive data
- Use environment variables for API keys
- Validate user inputs
- Implement proper authentication if needed

## Git Workflow
- Use descriptive commit messages in Arabic
- Create feature branches for new work
- Test changes before committing
- Follow conventional commit format when possible

## Development Tools
- ESLint for code linting
- Prettier for code formatting
- Use the provided npm scripts for development

## Documentation
- Add comments for complex logic
- Update README for significant changes
- Document API endpoints and data structures